                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/294: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Child</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-29T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1922—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>94. Your 102 June 26, 1 p.m.</p>
                <p>You will request the Italian Government, in view of its present position as
                    regards the control of shipments of arms to China, to indicate to this
                    Government, through you, its formal adoption of the amended resolution quoted in
                    the Department’s telegram No. 80 of June 3, 1 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
